\":{\"name\":\"Florence Filberg Centre\",\"location\":{\"city\":\"Courtenay\",\"country\":\"Canada\",\"latitude\":49.69247,\"longitude\":-124.99668,\"state\":\"BC\",\"street\":\"411 Anderton Ave\",\"zip\":\"V9N 6C6\"},\"id\":\"100343830030692\"},\"cover\":{\"offset_x\":0,\"offset_y\":19,\"source\":\"https:\\/\\/scontent.xx.fbcdn.net\\/v\\/t31.0-8\\/q84\\/s720x720\\/10830501_731290533621825_3743991282518717161_o.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=0e2222119f9f3ceb70457ce03124f130&oe=5B6C07C1\",\"id\":\"731290533621825\"},\"interested_count\":12},{\"name\":\"Campbell River Pottery Sale\",\"id\":\"666344890148334\",\"attending_count\":16,\"description\":\"Kick off the holiday season with some beautiful hand crafted pottery.  \\nOver 20 potters under one roof.  From the very functional to the very sculptural - something for every one and every budget.  \\nDoor prizes galore, coffee and cookies for a donation to potters helping potters, raffle for a gorgeous handmade quilt.  \\nCome join this festive atmosphere and find something for that hard to buy for person, or yourself.\",\"start_time\":\"2014-11-08T11:00:00-0800\",\"end_time\":\"2014-11-08T16:00:00-0800\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Vancouver\",\"cover\":{\"offset_x\":0,\"offset_y\":38,\"source\":\"https:\\/\\/scontent.xx.fbcdn.net\\/v\\/t1.0-9\\/10469318_10152829192291882_2628114160449861917_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=7476e15b53d66f8ab062e4c920861cf5&oe=5B338347\",\"id\":\"10152829192291882\"},\"interested_count\":6},{\"name\":\"Comox Valley Potters Clearance and Seconds Sale\",\"id\":\"482272735216202\",\"attending_count\":33,\"description\":\"Did you miss the holiday sale?  Can\'t get enough pottery?  Don\'t mind pottery that is shy of perfect?  Starting shopping for next year?\\nThis is a sale where potters sell everything from new creations, to discontinued lines, to less than perfect pots.  You are sure to find a treasure at discounted prices.  Pieces are arranged together and there is central cash.  \\nGet there early for best selection!\\nFriday February 14 9am-9pm and Saturday February 15 9am-5pm.\",\"start_time\":\"2014-02-14T09:00:00-0800\",\"end_time\":\"2014-02-15T17:00:00-0800\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Vancouver\",\"place\":{\"name\":\"Driftwood Mall\",\"location\":{\"city\":\"Courtenay\",\"country\":\"Canada\",\"latitude\":49.673663275344,\"located_in\":\"349581398421740\",\"longitude\":-124.98408428667,\"state\":\"BC\",\"street\":\"2751 Cliffe Ave # 1500\",\"zip\":\"V9N 2L8\"},\"id\":\"319967201357696\"},\"cover\":{\"offset_x\":0,\"offset_y\":56,\"source\":\"https:\\/\\/scontent.xx.fbcdn.net\\/v\\/t31.0-8\\/s720x720\\/1506151_568801663204047_381348363_o.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=3a2ce6422abc67e987f1225b0165f22a&oe=5B67B4C3\",\"id\":\"568801663204047\"},\"interested_count\":12},{\"name\":\"Comox Valley Potters Sale\",\"id\":\"225002887665488\",\"attending_count\":5,\"description\":\"A holiday tradition!  Come join us at the 22nd annual Potters sale. \\nOver 20 potters under one roof in downtown Courtenay.  Featuring the work of some of the finest potters in the country.\\nPartial proceeds will be donated to the Comox Valley Food Bank.  Donations of non-perishable food items will also be gratefully accepted.  \\nComox Valley - BC\'s Pottery Mecca.\",\"start_time\":\"2013-11-23T11:00:00-0800\",\"end_time\":\"2013-11-23T16:00:00-0800\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Vancouver\",\"place\":{\"name\":\"Florence Filberg Centre - Downtown Courtenay\"},\"cover\":{\"offset_x\":0,\"offset_y\":43,\"source\":\"https:\\/\\/scontent.xx.fbcdn.net\\/v\\/t1.0-9\\/1460011_541639089253638_342143762_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=bd75cb897e5ffb46aa18f80fd864a325&oe=5B30BE8A\",\"id\":\"541639089253638\"},\"interested_count\":1},{\"name\":\"Sarah Lawless Workshop\",\"id\":\"657621904341248\",\"attending_count\":1,\"description\":\"SARAH LAWLESS WORKSHOP\\n\\n\\nPresented by\\n\\n\\nTHE COMOX VALLEY POTTERS CLUB\\n\\n\\\"Thinking outside the circle; free-form functional pots made on a wheel\\\".  Throwing forms for altering.  Cutting, piercing, squishing and assembling.  The incorporation of slabs & hump-molds and non-traditional feet.  Considering function and ergonomics.\\n\\nDate:  May 12 & 13, 2012\\nTime:  10:00 am to 4:00 pm\\nLocation:  North Island College Ceramic Studio\\nEarly Bird Deadline:  April 28, 2012 \\nEarly Bird Fee:  CVPC members - $55.00  \\n                            Non members - $65.00\\n\\nFee after April 28, 2012:  CVPC members - $70.00  \\n                                           Non members - $80.00\\n\\n\\nPlease bring something for the potluck lunch both days and if possible, your own plate, cup and utensils.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSarah creates a line of porcelain ceramics, combining ergonomic usability with a sculptural emphasis on form. Her pots are thrown on a wheel and altered into imaginative \\ufb02uid forms with soft matte surfaces and earth-toned glazes. \\nShe worked as assistant to acclaimed potter Wayne Ngan, and has a Diploma in Craft and Design from Kootenay School of the Arts in Nelson, BC. Her work has been exhibited both nationally and internationally, and has earned her several awards, including a 2008 BC Creative Achievement Award.\",\"start_time\":\"2012-05-12T10:00:00-0700\",\"end_time\":\"2012-05-13T16:00:00-0700\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Los_Angeles\",\"place\":{\"name\":\"North Island College - Comox Valley Campus\",\"location\":{\"city\":\"Courtenay\",\"country\":\"Canada\",\"latitude\":49.710528557166,\"longitude\":-124.97126178523,\"state\":\"BC\",\"street\":\"2300 Ryan Road\",\"zip\":\"V9N 8N6\"},\"id\":\"211196932225358\"},\"interested_count\":0},{\"name\":\"Laurie Rowland Workshop\",\"id\":\"864688050271389\",\"attending_count\":0,\"description\":\"LAURIE ROLLAND WORKSHOP\\n\\nHandbuilding Workshop\\nForm and Surface\\n\\nPresented by\\n\\nTHE COMOX VALLEY POTTERS CLUB\\n\\nDate:  April 28 & 29, 2012\\nTime:  10:00 am to 4:00 pm\\nLocation:  North Island College Ceramic Studio\\nEarly Bird Deadline:  April 11, 2012\\nEarly Bird Fee:  CVPC members - $65.00, Non members - $75.00\\nFee after April 11, 2012:  CVPC members - $80.00, Non members - $90.00\\n\\nPlease bring something for the potluck lunch and if possible, your own plate, cup and utensils.\\n\\n\\n\\nThis workshop will show the unique hand building techniques that I have developed to enhance electric kiln firing in Oxidation. Using discussion, slides and demonstration, I will share the process I use to make these non-functional vessels.\",\"start_time\":\"2012-04-28T10:00:00-0700\",\"end_time\":\"2012-04-29T16:00:00-0700\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Los_Angeles\",\"place\":{\"name\":\"North Island College - Comox Valley Campus\",\"location\":{\"city\":\"Courtenay\",\"country\":\"Canada\",\"latitude\":49.710528557166,\"longitude\":-124.97126178523,\"state\":\"BC\",\"street\":\"2300 Ryan Road\",\"zip\":\"V9N 8N6\"},\"id\":\"211196932225358\"},\"interested_count\":0},{\"name\":\"Comox Valley Potters Club Clearance Sale\",\"id\":\"657844327649708\",\"attending_count\":1,\"description\":\"Missed the holiday sale?  Can\'t get enough pottery?  Check out the Comox Valley Potters Club clearance sale at Driftwood Mall Friday January 27 9am-9pm and Saturday January 28 9am-5pm.  Some seconds and discontinued items at great prices.\\nAll potters club profits go to Comox Valley Arts Council\",\"start_time\":\"2012-01-27T09:00:00-0800\",\"end_time\":\"2012-01-28T17:00:00-0800\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Los_Angeles\",\"interested_count\":0},{\"name\":\"Comox Valley Potters Club Holiday Sale (Courtenay)\",\"id\":\"1040551279308109\",\"attending_count\":5,\"description\":\"Come prepared to do your holiday shopping.  Beautiful art and functional pieces made by a variety of potters from in and around the Comox Valley.\",\"start_time\":\"2011-11-26T11:00:00-0800\",\"end_time\":\"2011-11-26T14:00:00-0800\",\"timezone\":\"America\\/Los_Angeles\",\"interested_count\":4},{\"name\":\"Comox Valley Potters Club Holiday Sale (Campbell River)\",\"id\":\"1121600837866037\",\"att